  <a href="#1" id="1">
   A strong earthquake triggered landslides and destroyed houses in the mountainous India-Nepal border region early Sunday, killing at least 237 people and injuring more than 1,500, officials and news reports said.
  </a>
  <a href="#2" id="2">
   Seismologists said it was the deadliest earthquake to strike the Himalayan region since 1950.
  </a>
  <a href="#3" id="3">
   Geological Survey monitors in Golden, Colo., recorded the earthquake at a preliminary magnitude of 6.7 on the Richter scale.
  </a>
  <a href="#4" id="4">
   The Richter scale gauges the energy released by an earthquake as measured by the ground motion recorded on a seismograph.
  </a>
  <a href="#5" id="5">
   Earthquakes are common in the Himalayan region.
  </a>
  <a href="#6" id="6">
   India's worst earthquake was in 1950, when at least 30,000 people were killed in Assam state.
